ing hypothetical long range plans across a variety of potential industries Provide hands-on deep analytic support and develop actionable insights that influence key decision makers Research and assess market opportunities and emerging business models Build and monitor forecasts and benchmark performance internally and externally while understanding the sources of deviation Convert quantitative analysis into qualitative presentation materials to present to business leaders across Facebook Identify and track financial KPIs understand and define key financial drivers of the business Build resource allocation analyses to drive better investment decisions, mitigate risks, and optimize long-term growth Minimum Qualifications 3+ years of experience in management consulting, investment banking, private equity, and/or business strategy Experience building advanced financial models, including P&L, balance sheet and cash flow projections Experience in Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint Experience synthesizing strategic insights and problem-solving individually or in a group setting, knowledge with financial drivers of the business Preferred Qualifications BA/BS in Engineering, Computer Science, Math, Economics, Statistics, or other quantitative field Experience in payments and/or financial technology Experience using SQL to build and maintain business-oriented data infrastructure Experienced using data manipulation and visualization/BI tools Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started. Facebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at accommodations-ext@fb.com. ", 
